    "text": "Erdős Problem #774: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. We call $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ dissociated if $\\sum_{n\\in X}n\\neq \\sum_{m\\in Y}m$ for all finite $X,Y\\subset A$ with $X\\neq Y$.\n\nLet $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ be an infinite set. We call $A$ proportionately dissociated if every finite $B\\subset A$ contains a dissociated set of size $\\gg \\lvert B\\rvert$.\n\nIs every proportionately dissociated set the union of a finite number of dissociated sets? Prize: no. Tags: number theory.",
